      "title": "The Space Children (1958)",
      "description": "The Space Children is a science-fiction film directed by Jack Arnold and features a cast that includes Michel Ray, Jackie Coogan, and Russell Johnson. The story revolves around a group of children living near a military base working on a rocket called \"The Thunderer,\" designed to launch a nuclear device into orbit. The children encounter a small alien life form that communicates with them telepathically. Under its influence, they embark on a mission to sabotage the rocket launch, believing it poses a threat to humanity. The film addresses themes of nuclear fear and the innocence of childhood. It presents a pacifist message, suggesting that children can recognize the dangers of nuclear weapons better than adults. While it has been critiqued for its low budget and simplistic plot, it remains a notable example of 1950s sci-fi cinema.",
      "id": "the.-space.-children.-1958"
